From 76561d6a667436d200ef7b35f1443748e4f6f02c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 11:10:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(api): centralize admin auth into withAdminAuth
 wrapper

- Add lib/with-auth.ts (withAuth, withAdminAuth) that resolves the
  session, checks the role, resolves route params, and centralizes
  error logging + the generic 500 response.
- Migrate all 24 admin API routes (movies, series + nested
  seasons/episodes, tags, requests, reports, featured, featured-series,
  tmdb, stats, most-favorited, recent-signups) and upload/file to use it,
  removing the copy-pasted
    const session = await getCachedSession(request);
    if (!session || session.user.role !== "admin") { ... }
  block from every file.
- Fix copy-paste bug in admin/series/[id]/route.ts where a series ID
  was stored in a variable named movieId (PUT and DELETE).
- Standardize all series admin routes on NextResponse.json instead of
  the bare Response.json that had crept in.
- Remove lib/session.ts#requireAdmin, a helper that duplicated the same
  logic but was never actually called anywhere (dead code).
- Replace 'catch (err: any)' with 'catch (err)' + instanceof check in
  admin/series/route.ts.

Net: -752 / +435 lines. Verified with tsc --noEmit and eslint, both
clean.
